Apostle Johnson Suleman of the Omega Fire Ministries, Auchi, Edo State, has reacted to Arsenal’s latest signing, Fabio Vieira. Earlier this week, Arsenal confirmed the signing of Vieira from former FC Porto. Vieira joined Arsenal after the completion of a £34 million deal with Porto. The deal includes an initial fee of €35m (£30m) in addition to €5m (£4.3m) worth of add-ons. Reacting, Suleman, a passionate Arsenal fan, in a tweet via his Twitter handle, on Friday described Vieira, as a fine player who has both characteristics of Manchester City duo, Bernado Silva and Kevin De Bruyne. According to him, Arsenal will have a good 2022/23 season after signing Vieira. He tweeted: “So Arsenal has signed both B Silva and KDB in Fabio Vieira..fine player..striker, winger..1 more DM and Arsenal should have a good session. “Chelsea and Man U Weldone..”